{{wikipedia}}
==English==
[[Image:Liocarcinus vernalis.jpg|thumb|A crab]]
===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[crabbe]]'', from Old English ''[[crabba]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æb|-æb]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[crustacean]] of the [[infraorder]] ''[[Brachyura]]'', having five pairs of legs, the [[foremost]] of which are in the form of [[claw]]s, and a [[carapace]].
# A [[bad-tempered]] person.
# (''in plural'' '''crabs'''; ''informal'') [[pubic lice]].
# {{slang}} a twenty pence piece. So named because they are seven sided and there is an [[urban myth]] that crabs have a seventh [[leg]] they keep inside their [[shell]] for [[emergencies]].

====Derived terms====
*[[hermit crab]]
*[[horseshoe crab]]

